[Re: 22 Sep 2001: "Dengue fever cases hit 415: disease past its peak and
under control, say health authorities..."]
Macau health authorities said on Wednesday that about 700 cases have been
reported since the end of August 2001, of which 695 have been confirmed
since 30 Aug 2001. From 20-25 cases daily have been confirmed in recent
weeks, of whom 50 remain hospitalized.
